   b_i < b_{i+1}

If we set b_i=0, then we require b_{i+1} to be at least 1? but b_{i+1} must be a multiple of a_{i+1]. The smallest positive multiple is a_{i+1] (if we set k_{i+1}=1) -> then 0 < a_{i+1] -> which is true. But what if we set b_i to 0, then the left part: we have to set b_{i-1] to a negative value? The constraint: b_{i-1] < b_i = 0. The minimal cost for b_{i-1] is to set it to the smallest nonnegative multiple? but that would be 0 -> then 0<0 is false. So we must set it to a negative multiple. The largest negative multiple (closest to 0) is -a_{i-1] (by subtracting once) -> cost 1. Then we have -a_{i-1] < 0 -> true. But then the element to the left of that: we set to -2*a_{i-2]?

